<p>Our experienced team at Al Miley & Associates has the necessary skills to remove unwanted trees and shrubs, allowing your landscape to flourish. Why is tree and shrub removal so necessary? By removing unwanted trees and shrubs, there will be less competition for soil nutrients and sunlight by the remaining trees. You will also have a less-congested and cleaner looking landscape. Removing unwanted trees and shrubs also gives you an opportunity to re-design your garden and to improve accessibility to the woods.</p>
<p>We use the precise and less-invasive tree and shrub removal procedures. We will ensure that we limit the impact on the soil. We will also limit the level of intrusion to your landscape. We avoid using invasive machinery like bulldozers. Instead, we take the necessary precautions to protect your landscape. Tree and shrub removal helps to increase air circulation within the branches and promotes new healthy growth of trees. Our main objective is to make your environment more attractive and safer.</p>
 <a href="https://www.almileytree.com/emergency-tree-shrub-removal-toronto/" title="Emergency Tree &amp; Shrub Removal">Read More</a>";s:6:"filter";b:0;}i:15;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:20:"Tree & Shrub Pruning";s:4:"text";s:1295:"<img class="square" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/tree_care_05-02.png"/>
<p>A tree may seem invincible and capable of surviving under any circumstances. However, it is important to note that, just like any other living organisms, trees need assistance to thrive effectively. The main ways you can boost the health of your trees and shrubs are through pruning and fertilizing. Pruning is essential in helping trees and shrubs thrive outside their natural growing environment in the wild. Pruning enables you to maintain the aesthetics of your trees and makes trees to develop a durable structure. </p>
<p>Through pruning, you can effectively get rid of diseased or sickly plant parts. It helps prevent the disease from spreading to the entire tree. You will also be able to control harmful insects by pruning your trees; the insects will not have hiding places. You should note that improper pruning might cause severe damage and even contribute to the death of your tree. Therefore, you should only have a professional prune your trees and shrubs. With our experienced pruning experts at Al Miley & Associates, nothing can go wrong.  </p>
<a href="https://www.almileytree.com/tree-and-shrub-pruning-trimming-toronto/" title="Tree and Shrub Pruning">Read More</a>";s:6:"filter";b:0;}i:16;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:24:"Storm Damage Restoration";s:4:"text";s:1280:"<img class="square" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/storm_damage_cleanup_05-02.png"/>
<p>How you respond after a storm makes the difference between giving your trees a chance of survival or losing your valued trees. After a storm, you may notice that large tree branches and limbs are hanging and broken. It is advisable to contact storm damage restoration experts like Al Miley & Associates to help you restore the trees. We have all the necessary tools and expertise, and we will know the right course of action to take. We will remove the remains of smaller broken limbs to minimize the risk of decay spreading to the main trunk. </p>
<p>To help improve the aesthetics of the tree and to eliminate places where insects can hide, we will repair the torn tree bark. In parts where the back is torn away, we will use the right equipment to smooth the ragged edges of the wound. The tree's appearance may not be perfect at first. However, we will avoid over-pruning because, with time, the branches will grow to restore the beauty of the tree. You do not have to give up on your trees after storm damage; we can help restore their glamour.</p>
<a href="https://www.almileytree.com/tree-restoration-toronto/" title="Storm Damage Removal">Read More</a>";s:6:"filter";b:0;}i:17;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:17:"Vertical Mulching";s:4:"text";s:1760:"<img class="square" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/tree_care_06-02.png"/>
<p>Your trees could greatly benefit from vertical mulching services from Al Miley & Associates. Vertical mulching is a popular procedure that entails drilling tiny holes in the soil beneath the canopy of a tree. We ensure the small holes extend all the way to the tree protection zone or drip line. We then fill the holes with the right mixtures of mulch, including leaves, wood chips, and pine straw, among others. We may also include other materials like pea gravel, sand, or compost. </p>
<p>Your trees could greatly benefit from vertical mulching services from Al Miley & Associates. Vertical mulching is a popular procedure that entails drilling tiny holes in the soil beneath the canopy of a tree. We ensure the small holes extend all the way to the tree protection zone or drip line. We then fill the holes with the right mixtures of mulch, including leaves, wood chips, and pine straw, among others. We may also include other materials like pea gravel, sand, or compost. 
What are the main benefits of vertical mulching? This procedure helps to increase the oxygen levels in the soil by improving aeration. Vertical mulching also helps to reduce soil compaction and allows tree roots to spread freely. The procedure will help to inoculate the root zone of stressed shrubs or trees. Your trees will also thrive better because the procedure helps to fertilize the soil and add essential nutrients. Sub-soil water will penetrate better, reducing the chances of excessive watering, which may be harmful to your trees.</p>


 <a href="https://www.almileytree.com/vertical-mulching-soil-aeration-toronto/" title="Vertical Mulching">Read More</a></p>";s:6:"filter";b:0;}i:18;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:38:"Arborist Report By Certified Arborists";s:4:"text";s:1306:"<img class="square" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/arborist_report_05-02.png" />
<p>At Al Miley & Associates, we can provide you with an objective arborist report that will offer invaluable insight into the condition of your trees and shrubs. An arborist report outlines the condition of trees, including the presence of pests and threats of diseases. The report also outlines the site conditions and mechanical injuries, if any. The reports also offer some recommendations to help your trees thrive. The recommendations may include treating root issues, pest control, injections or fertilization, and site remediation. </p>
<p>Why is an arborist report essential? The report will offer insight into the condition and the health of your trees. It will also outline the root cause of problems like diseases and recommend actions you can take to alleviate the problems. The report also offers insight into the trees you can take down without inflicting undue loss to the community. Before you take down trees, most city authorities require you to have an arborist report.  Contact us today to meet with one of our experienced arborists.</p>

<a href="https://www.almileytree.com/arborist-report-consultation-toronto/" title="Arborist Report" target="_blank">Read More</a></p>";s:6:"filter";b:0;}i:19;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:22:"Tree Cabling & Bracing";s:4:"text";s:1226:"<img class="square" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/tree_cabling-02.png" />
<p>If you notice that some of your trees have become weak and unstable, it may be time to consider tree cabling and bracing. Typically, trees may become unstable due to uneven damage and growth, making the trees unable to support their own weight. Unstable trees may pose a risk of property damage and personal injuries due to falling trees. At Al Miley & Associates, we do not restrict cabling and bracing to the big trees only. We also consider the smaller trees because cabling and bracing help to enhance proper growth and stability. </p>
<p>Proper cabling and bracing will help to promote the long-term health of your trees. In any commercial and residential property, trees are an important asset, and enhancing their longevity will help them serve you for a long time. You will enjoy the shade and the cool breeze from the trees for longer. You will not have to incur frequent tree removal and tree replacement costs. You can focus that money on other areas of your property maintenance.</p>

<a href="https://www.almileytree.com/tree-cabling-and-bracing-toronto/" title="Tree Cabling and Bracing">Read More</a>";s:6:"filter";b:0;}i:20;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:18:"Tree Crane Service";s:4:"text";s:1221:"<img class="square" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/stump-removal-icon-1.png" />
<p>Al Miley & Associates offers a reliable tree crane service in Toronto. The use of cranes in tree removal is the new trend, and companies are no longer using traditional tree removal services. The benefits of tree crane service are its effectiveness and saving on time. It will take less time to remove trees smartly and safely. The use of crane will also have less impact on your landscape. There will be fewer chances of risks and injuries associated with traditional tree removal services. </p>
<p>At  Al Miley & Associates, we have state-of-the-art cranes that are very effective. The cranes are mounted on trucks capable of moving at high speeds. The use of fast trucks means less time removing the trees. The strength of our cranes lies in their lifting capacity, versatility, and reach. Our cranes can access any trees no matter how hidden they are and irrespective of the tightness of the quarters. We offer timely tree removal services, and we never keep our customers waiting.</p>

<a href="https://www.almileytree.com/tree-crane-service/" title="Tree Crane Service" target="_blank">Read More</a>";s:6:"filter";b:0;}i:21;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:12:"Lot Clearing";s:4:"text";s:1224:"<img class="square" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/lot-clearing-2.png" />

<p>Al Miley & Associates provides lot-clearing services to enhance the safety and accessibility of your landscape. Lot clearing entails clearing trees and shrubs. Other than enhancing safety, lot clearing may also help make way for new lawn expansion, renovations, and constructions. The key benefit of lot clearing is improving the aesthetics of your landscape and creating more space. If trees and shrubs are growing in the wrong areas and if they are too close together, they may detract the value of your property. By clearing the overgrown areas, you can add other amenities like outdoor living spaces. </p>
<p>Lot clearing helps to improve the safety and the health of your property. If you leave unattended weedy and brushy areas, they may act as thriving places for rodents, snakes, or even bigger animals. These animals may bring unwanted diseases or insects. The animals may also pose a hazard, especially when you are driving. Our lot clearing services will help offer you a safer environment.</p>
<a href="https://www.almileytree.com/lot-clearing-tree/" title="Lot Clearing" target="_blank">Read More</a>";s:6:"filter";b:0;}i:22;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:24:"Stump Removal & Grinding";s:4:"text";s:1191:"<img class="square" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/stump-removal-icon-2.png" />
<p>Once you successfully remove a tree, what will remain is a tree stump. You may wonder what to do with the tree stump. For instance, should you just leave the stump lying on the yard or grind it? Leaving a tree stump in your yard may pose a great nuisance. The stump can be a trip hazard for you and your family members. A stump may also get in the way of mowing your lawn. With tree removal and grinding services from Al Miley & Associates, tree stumps do not have to be a nuisance.  </p>
<p>Our tree removal and grinding services will offer you a wide range of benefits, including enhancing the aesthetics of your yard. Our services will also help improve the convenience and safety of your yard. You will be able to avoid unwanted growth and pests. If you fail to remove a tree stump, new untidy stocks may sprout from the stump. Stump grinding is less invasive than stump removal and will not have adverse effects on your landscape.</p>
